2025-11-06 | Check Prefix Binary Numbers Divisible by 5

Problem Statement  
You are given a binary array `nums`.
Define:  
`xi` = decimal value of the binary number represented by `nums[0..i]`  
(i.e., prefix from index 0 to i)

Return a boolean array where `answer[i]` is true if `xi` is divisible by **5**, otherwise false

Approach / Explanation  
1. Prefix Number Growth  
If you have a number `x`, and you append a bit `b` (0 or 1), the new number becomes:  
x_new = (x * 2 + b)

2. Modulo Trick  
We never need the entire number — only whether it is divisible by 5.  
So instead of storing huge numbers, we keep:  
x_mod = (x_mod * 2 + b) % 5

3. Each prefix check  
If `x_mod == 0`, then the current prefix integer is divisible by 5.

4. Complexity  
• Time: O(n)  
• Space: O(1) extra, aside from output

SOLUTION:
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    vector<bool> prefixesDivBy5(vector<int>& nums) {
        vector<bool> ans;
        int mod = 0;

        for (int bit : nums) {
            mod = (mod * 2 + bit) % 5;
            ans.push_back(mod == 0);
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
